diff:1614463949:1614463949:=1,44d0%0a%3c :Category: TypologyOfPhoneticContrasts%0a%3c :Expansion: Training Catalan Speakers to Identify L2 Consonants and Vowels Study%0a%3c :Author: JasonE%0a%3c :Original: [[Articles.PresenceOfUncommonConsonantsComparingEnglishAndCatalan|PresenceOfUncommonConsonantsComparingEnglishAndCatalan]] %0a%3c :OriginalAuthor: [[Profiles.bellar|bellar]]%0a%3c :Section: %0a%3c :Completed: 27.02.2021 - 14:12%0a%3c :Status: ungraded%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %25red%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#history]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#historyend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c %25red%25 '''Comments to student'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#comments]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#commentsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c !!%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c This study was performed on Catalan-spanish bilinguals and attempts to train second language (L2) speakers how to acquire sounds that are not found in their first language (L1). The study was performed on bilinguals who speak Catalan-spanish and English. This relates to Bella’s article as there are certain consonants that are in the English language, but not in Catalan-spanish, which makes it difficult for some L2 speakers to learn these sounds.%0a%3c %0a%3c The results of the study indicate that after the 3-week phonetic training program, the speakers improved the vowel sounds /i/ and /ʌ/ and the consonants /b/, /v/ and /d/. However, no significant improvements were found for the sounds: /ɪ/, /æ/ and /ð/. As Bella said in her previous post, /ð/ is a sound that is non-existent in Catalan-spanish, but it is found in the English language. Therefore, it is not shocking that L2 speakers had a challenging time improving their pronunciation of this sound. I found it interesting that L2 speakers were able to improve their pronunciation of multiple vowel sounds as I believe that those sounds are more difficult to master.%0a%3c %0a%3c Source:%0a%3c Carlet, A., & Cebrian, J. (2014). Training Catalan Speakers to Identify L2 Consonants and Vowels: A Short-Term High Variability Training Study. Retrieved February 27, 2021, from http://doe.concordia.ca/copal/documents/8_Carlet_Cebrian_Vol5.pdf%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:Category:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
